1Ô∏è‚É£ S3 (Simple Storage Service)
Q1. How do you make an S3 bucket public for static website hosting?
Answer:Enable static website hosting in bucket properties.
Use Bucket Policy to allow public GetObject access.
Enable public access settings (disable ‚ÄúBlock Public Access‚Äù).
Q2. Why do public access and bucket policies both matter?
Answer:Public access settings: account-level safety check.
Bucket policy: resource-level permissions.
Both are required to make a bucket accessible externally.
Q3. What happens if you delete files in S3?
Answer:Files are removed from S3.
Lambda functions triggered by uploads still exist.
CloudWatch logs remain unaffected.
Q4. Why must S3 bucket names be globally unique?
Answer:S3 namespace is shared across all AWS accounts worldwide.
Duplicate bucket names cause BucketAlreadyExists errors.
2Ô∏è‚É£ CloudWatch (Monitoring & Alarms)
Q1. What is Amazon CloudWatch?
Answer:A monitoring service to collect metrics, logs, and events for AWS resources.
Can trigger alarms based on thresholds.
Q2. Which EC2 metrics are available by default?
Answer:CPUUtilization, NetworkIn/Out, DiskReadOps/DiskWriteOps.
Q3. What happens when a CloudWatch alarm triggers?
Answer:Alarm state changes (OK ‚Üí ALARM).
Can send notifications via SNS or trigger actions like auto scaling.
Q4. How did you test your CloudWatch alarm?
Answer:Generated CPU load using stress tool on EC2.
Verified state changed and email notification received.
Q5. Difference between metrics and logs?
Answer:Metrics: numeric performance data (CPU, network).
Logs: text/application output for debugging and analysis.
3Ô∏è‚É£ AWS CLI (Command Line Interface)
Q1. What is AWS CLI and why use it?
Answer:Command-line tool for managing AWS programmatically.
Enables automation, scripting, and faster operations than console.
Q2. What credentials are required for AWS CLI?
Answer:Access Key ID + Secret Access Key of an IAM user.
Region and output format (json, table, text).
Q3. Why avoid root user access keys?
Answer:Root has full privileges; using it is a security risk.
IAM users/roles with least privilege are recommended.
Q4. Why did S3 bucket creation fail?
Answer:Bucket names are globally unique; someone else already owns that name.
Q5. How to verify AWS CLI is configured correctly?
Answer:Run aws s3 ls or aws ec2 describe-instances and check output.
4Ô∏è‚É£ Lambda (Serverless)
Q1. What is AWS Lambda?
Answer:Serverless compute service, runs code in response to events.
No server management; pay only for execution time.
Q2. How did you trigger your Lambda function?
Answer:Using S3 ObjectCreated event.
Uploading a file automatically invokes Lambda.
Q3. Where do Lambda logs go?
Answer:Logs are sent to CloudWatch Logs automatically.
Q4. What role does IAM play in Lambda execution?
Answer:Lambda assumes an IAM execution role to access AWS services and write logs.
Q5. Real-time use cases of Lambda?
Answer:Image resizing, log processing, data transformation, CI/CD triggers.
Q6. Does deleting S3 files remove Lambda logs?
Answer:No, CloudWatch logs remain until retention policy expires or manual deletion.

